comments[7]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-06T22:11:13.026Z",maintainer-agent,"Prior-art note (audit #15 follow-up): unbraind already ships pm-starter and pm-ts-starter (reference EXTENSIONS covering all capability types). This exemplar is deliberately different — a standalone custom PM tool composed only from public SDK primitives, not an extension scaffold. Reference the starters for structure/CI conventions, do not duplicate them; if the exemplar drifts toward 'reference extension', fold it into pm-ts-starter upstream instead."
  "2026-07-07T08:58:20.674Z",codex-agent,"Progress evidence: active PR bundle contributes SDK-only exemplar readiness by documenting and manually proving hermetic package doctor flows for package authors. This is evidence for the eventual SDK-only custom PM tool, not full exemplar completion; close remains dependent on the full exemplar package."
  "2026-07-07T09:44:05.259Z",codex-agent,"Package exemplar update: pm-6abs verifies package doctor isolation and docs now describe hermetic package-author smoke tests, reducing machine-local global extension leakage during package development."
  "2026-07-08T06:06:38.653Z",codex,"Evidence: agent-facing SDK ergonomics improved by exporting concrete lifecycle result contracts from the public SDK instead of forcing package authors to handle unknown returns for common mutation primitives."
  "2026-07-16T20:25:23.492Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260716,"Implementation start 2026-07-16: build the canonical SDK-only custom PM tool exemplar as a tested package using public @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk exports only; cover customization, lifecycle, annotations, queries, governance, and context."
  "2026-07-16T20:48:19.533Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260716,"Coverage integration finding: packages/pm-* is the installable extension catalog boundary. The SDK-only package exemplar now lives under docs/examples so it remains packed, typechecked, runnable, and independent without becoming a wildcard-install target."
  "2026-07-16T21:18:28.456Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260716,"Evidence: added docs/examples/sdk-custom-tool as a standalone package-shaped consumer importing only @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk. It composes custom type/status registration, create/update/claim/release/close, annotations, linked resources, list/search/context, dependency graph, health, and history validation. Packed @unbrained/pm-cli acceptance in /tmp/pm-sdk-wide-pack-U7vgr1 returned Deliverable/reviewing/closed, activeItemsBeforeClose=2, dependencyEdges=1, healthOk=true, historyDriftOk=true."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-16T21:18:31.145Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260716,Standalone SDK consumers belong outside packages/pm-* because that directory is the installable extension catalog boundary; docs/examples keeps the exemplar packed and typechecked without making it a wildcard extension-install target.
